arr = [1, 2, 4, 5, 3, 10, 9]
large = float('-inf')
second = float('-inf')
for num in arr:
    if num > large:
        second = large
        large = num
    elif num > second and num < large:
        second = num

print(second)

Note: why we use float('inf')? --> for representating smallest element we use the float('-inf') as well as for representating the largest element we use the float('inf'). if we use arr[0] instead of float('-inf'), it might fail in the cases of duplicates. 
